project.name: Blocks Domain v2
project.description: This project represents the classical Blocks World domain.

actor.name: Hand
actor.description: This actor is responsible for changing the arrangement of the blocks among the tables.

useCase.name: Stack block
useCase.description: The agent hand stacks a block, putting it on another block, which is the top one of an existing pile of blocks at a table.

definition.precondition: - the hand must be holding the block at a table; - the pile where the block is to be put must at the same table as the hand.
definition.invariants: - the block and the hand remains at the same table.

useCase.name: Unstack block
useCase.description: The agent hand unstack the top block of a pile at a table.

definition.postcondition: - the hand is holding the block; - the block which was under the unstacked block is clear, i. e., the pile has a new top block.
definition.invariants: - the block and the hand remains at the same table.

useCase.name: Pick up block
useCase.description: The agent hand pick up a block from a table.

definition.postcondition: - the hand is holding the block;
definition.invariants: - the block and the hand remains at the same table.

useCase.name: Put down block
useCase.description: The agent hand puts a block on a table.

definition.precondition: - the hand must be holding the block at a table.
definition.postcondition: - the block is clear and on the table; - the hand is empty.
definition.invariants: - the block and the hand remains at the same table.

useCase.name: Change table
useCase.description: The agent hand change the table at where it is.

definition.postcondition: - the hand is at the destination table; - the origin table is available.
definition.invariants: - if the hand is holding a block then it remains holding the same block; - if the hand is empty then it remains empty.

state.name: Block x clear on a block y at a Table table
state.condition: x.on = y and x.ontable = null and x.attable = table

state.name: Hand hand holding block x
state.condition: x.clear = false and x.on = null and x.ontable = null and x.attable = null

state.name: Block x on the Table table
state.condition: x.on = null and x.ontable = table and x.attable = table

state.name: Hand holding Block x at a table

action.precondition: hand.at = tablefrom and tableto.available = true and hand.hasAccessTo->includes(tableto)
action.postcondition: hand.at = tableto and tablefrom.available = true and tableto.available = false

action.precondition: hand.at = tablefrom and tableto.available = true and hand.hasAccessTo->includes(tableto)
action.postcondition: hand.at = tableto and tablefrom.available = true and tableto.available = false

problem.name: Three Blocks
problem.description: This a classic blocks domain problem with just three blocks and one table

problem.name: Thirteen Blocks Five Tables and Two Hands
